						<summary>

						<p>Stone set up in the prākāra of Māṅgōḍu Subbarāya temple.</p>						

						<p>The record is very badly damaged. It refers to the installation of Śanidēva in the <hi rend="italic">maṭha</hi> built by Nārāyaṇa-pādirāya, grandson of Halaṇasenabōva and mentions the <hi rend="italic">jagattu</hi> and the village Kutupāḍi.</p>						

						<p>It is dated cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Vikāri, Mīna 13, Monday,</hi> other details being lost. It is in modern characters.</p>						

						</summary>
